headline : Changing lives through household mentoring
text : \r\nIn Uganda, household mentoring offers hope to the poorest of the poor. Around 600 mentors have already helped to change the lives of some 20.000 vulnerable families, teaching them about sanitation, family planning and better farming techniques. After a close look, we talk to our Africa correspondent Edith Kimani about the project.\r\n
